TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=347
TASK_TITLE=Show assigned subtask on pane border status in tmux
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_DESCRIPTION=Each Claude pane in tmux should show which subtask it's currently working on. When a worker is assigned a subtask (e.g. 'W2.1: Research doey-term source...'), that subtask title should appear in the pane's border status line in tmux.

This likely involves:
1. The pane-border-status.sh script (shell/pane-border-status.sh) — this renders the pane border text
2. Status files in /tmp/doey/<project>/status/ — may need a 'subtask' field or file
3. The dispatch mechanism — when Subtaskmaster assigns a subtask to a worker, it should write the subtask info to a status file the border script reads

Check how pane-border-status.sh currently works, what data it reads, and add the subtask display. Format: show the subtask title (truncated if needed) after the pane role/name.
